Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.43,0:00:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This jam is really delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.87,0:00:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NIt's homemade lingonberry jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.37,0:00:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My, homemade!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.17,0:00:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I was asked to show this to\Ncustomers who particularly enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.81,0:00:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the maker of the jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.91,0:00:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this person?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.82,0:00:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is Conrad.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.39,0:00:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a place on the southern hill\Nwhere a lot of lingonberries grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.26,0:00:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we knew it,\Nthat whole area was his.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.56,0:00:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But no one complained because\Nhe made such good jam?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.83,0:00:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. He's a very pleasant man.\NHe's one of my few friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.34,0:00:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It was his idea to\Nshow his picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.54,0:01:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's his way of saying, please continue to\Nenjoy the Conrad-brand lingonberry jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.88,0:01:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That means that I have to\Ncome back here for this jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.69,0:01:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.89,0:01:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd be pleased\Nyou said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.86,0:03:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there really going to be\Nan attack on this peaceful town?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.24,0:03:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,An attack...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.74,0:03:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other methods.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.64,0:03:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a case in which a\Nsingle gun annihilated an entire town.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.68,0:03:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,1958, in Zweifelstadt.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.61,0:03:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a string of\Nserial murders in Lower Saxony.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.29,0:03:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The residents thought that\Ntheir neighbors might be serial killers
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.52,0:03:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and were paranoid over\Nordinary everyday occurrences.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.66,0:03:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Amidst the mass hysteria,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.43,0:03:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the residents obtained a gun\Nfor self-defense and shot his neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.60,0:03:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No one could control\Nwhat followed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.27,0:03:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A fire started in the town and\Neveryone held weapons by their side.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.08,0:03:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All of the residents killed each other.\NThere were no survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.01,0:03:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that's going to\Nhappen to this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.19,0:03:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got to stop it.. .\Nbefore that happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.09,0:04:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.23,0:04:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It may have already begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.04,0:04:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, give us your money!\NYou have some. Give it to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.31,0:04:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that money is for...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.81,0:04:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably money for\Nyour drunken dad's alcohol, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.35,0:04:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Drinking too much\Nisn't good for the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.08,0:04:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We're helping him.\NHelping.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.59,0:04:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's go eat\Nat the usual place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.62,0:04:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.32,0:04:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.83,0:04:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.93,0:04:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You hate them, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.54,0:04:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You hate them so much that\Nyou want to kill them, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.21,0:04:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going, dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.41,0:04:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to talk to Conrad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.12,0:05:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk to him? How?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.19,0:05:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When we passed the cafe,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.85,0:05:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't you notice that Ralph, the owner,\Nand the customers were smiling at us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.29,0:05:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because it was unusual\Nfor them to see us together, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.90,0:05:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No. If they knew that we won\N20 million marks on a lottery,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.97,0:05:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,who knows what they'd do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.17,0:05:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.34,0:05:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think it's better to talk to him than\Nto continue to be suspicious of him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.44,0:05:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Mr. Conrad might\Nknow that I won the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.32,0:05:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so,\Nwhat are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.62,0:05:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll pay him any amount\Nof money to keep him quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.62,0:05:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But Conrad is greedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.69,0:05:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What if he keeps on asking\Nfor money afterwards?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.63,0:05:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,W-When that happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.43,0:05:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What'll we do\Nwhen that happens?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.13,0:05:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.27,0:06:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Was this the area where\Nhe gathers lingonberries?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.51,0:06:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.78,0:06:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Conrad's not such\Na bad person, right dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.82,0:06:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.59,0:06:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not the sort of person who would\Nruin the luck we managed to seize, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.79,0:06:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.34,0:06:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.68,0:06:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,D-D-Dear, did you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.68,0:06:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.91,0:06:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing something\Nso irrevocable...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.02,0:06:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I said that it wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.52,0:06:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Then who did this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.39,0:06:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,H-How would I know?! I've\Nnever fired my gun since I bought it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.40,0:06:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.00,0:06:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That dog sure is annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.30,0:06:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt's getting on my nerves.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.71,0:07:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem in\Nhigh spirits today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.28,0:07:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Did something good\Nhappen to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.71,0:07:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He finally appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.52,0:07:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What finally appeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.39,0:07:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The wonderful person who will\Ntake me away from this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.63,0:07:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A drink...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.10,0:07:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,A drink...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.90,0:07:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Crap...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.67,0:07:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The townspeople...\NThey ridicule me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.24,0:07:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not funny at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.55,0:07:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A drink...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.82,0:07:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing that you want...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.63,0:08:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.07,0:08:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Your son has\Nalready taken one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.02,0:08:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.99,0:08:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog stopped barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.64,0:08:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That sure was interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.17,0:08:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Lipsky.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.58,0:08:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Franz Bonaparta's son,\Nright?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.72,0:08:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me where your father is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.28,0:08:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not a moment to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.12,0:08:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Something terrible will happen\Nif I don't hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.92,0:09:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You know where your father is,\Ndon't you, Mr. Lipsky?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.50,0:09:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That puppet is modeled\Non Nina, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.37,0:09:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina told me that\Nyou were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.64,0:09:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina told you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.31,0:09:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The curtain...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.81,0:09:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Please keep it open.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.48,0:09:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.88,0:09:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How long have I\Nbeen like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.56,0:09:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.42,0:09:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You should continue to rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.26,0:09:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. I get the feeling\Nthat you stayed by my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.87,0:09:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about me. I'm all right.\NI won't try to kill myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.01,0:09:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Reichwein and Dieter\Nshould be coming soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.78,0:09:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.41,0:09:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.02,0:10:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.02,0:10:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,"Where to"' huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.72,0:10:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You've gathered a lot of material and\Nhave been looking at it here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.96,0:10:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.19,0:10:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm okay, so tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.47,0:10:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been having former\Nsecret police in Prague
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.20,0:10:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and General Wolf's subordinates\Ngather whatever information they could.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.11,0:10:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,About Franz Bonaparta?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.41,0:10:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He was a very mysterious person,\Nbut little by little, I learned who he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.99,0:10:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a Czechoslovakian\Nof German decent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.65,0:10:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz Bonaparta\Nis also an alias.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.26,0:10:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,After World War Two,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.76,0:10:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,despite the fact that many\NCzechoslovakians of German descent
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.00,0:10:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,were driven out of\Ntheir homeland, Bohemia.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.97,0:10:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,His family remained\Nwithin the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.30,0:10:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not clear\Nwhat post he held
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.64,0:10:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in the government in\NCommunist Czechoslovakia.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.54,0:11:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that he was once married to\Na Czech woman and they had a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.18,0:11:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that that child participated\Nin the early stages of his "recitals"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.92,0:11:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,during the mid-sixties.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.93,0:11:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,"Bonaparta has\Na son in Prague."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.03,0:11:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that Peter Capek's\Nlast words refer to this son.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.94,0:11:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I managed to\Nget a hold of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.27,0:11:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a copy of an old photograph\Nthat shows the children
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.11,0:11:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,who participated in the "recitals"\Nin the mid-sixties.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.68,0:11:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that the boy\Nto the far left...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.22,0:11:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't a superior pupil...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.59,0:11:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.32,0:11:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't a superior pupil. ..\Nso he was expelled from the recitals.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.22,0:11:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.13,0:11:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He became of no use\Nto Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.73,0:11:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He's probably the man\NI know in Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.07,0:12:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think that this man knows\Nwhere his father.. .where Bonaparta is?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.87,0:12:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.44,0:12:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's our only lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.88,0:12:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't hurry,\Nsomething terrible will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.21,0:12:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Something terrible?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.51,0:12:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what Johan\Nis going to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.52,0:12:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What is he going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.52,0:12:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,A perfect suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.96,0:12:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,True solitude.\NThe only expression of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.73,0:12:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't hurry,\Nmany innocent people will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.51,0:12:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Your bookshelf...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.07,0:12:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's filled with picture books that were\Nwritten under Bonaparta's pseudonyms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.54,0:12:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I've also obtained and\Nread most of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.61,0:12:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,After reading several,\NI realized something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.82,0:12:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,For some reason, the characters in\Nhis books have German names.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.46,0:12:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in Klaus Poppe's\NThe God of Peace...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.29,0:13:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But the issue is the pen name,\N"Klaus Poppe."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.70,0:13:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz Bonaparta and his other\Npen names are all Czech names...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.84,0:13:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But only this name is German.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.14,0:13:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be that Klaus Poppe is your\NGerman-born Czech father's real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.39,0:13:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a detective who\Nmade the same deduction–
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.29,0:13:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was my father's\Nreal name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.89,0:13:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.06,0:13:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,An Inspector Lunge\Nof the BKA.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.56,0:13:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Lunge?! He's here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.20,0:13:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He left several weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.90,0:13:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Left?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.17,0:13:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He also figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.34,0:13:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Inspector Lunge\Nbecomes the person
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.87,0:13:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than\Nmaking deductions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.68,0:13:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,"I am Klaus Poppe."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.14,0:13:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,"I have no place\Nto go home to."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.68,0:13:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,"In order to regain\Nmy peace of mind"'
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.02,0:13:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,"I must return to my hometown\Nin my mind"' he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.79,0:13:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The German-born Czechs\Nwere chased out of Bohemia
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.89,0:14:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and lost their homeland\Nafter the Germans lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.39,0:14:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Where in Germany were\Nhis ancestors from?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.30,0:14:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.30,0:14:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I was a child,\Nmy father told me that our home
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.77,0:14:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,was a town surrounded\Nby mountains in southern Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.61,0:14:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't need that anymore,\Nso I gave it to Inspector Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.51,0:14:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A postcard that was sent to me\Nthree or four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.88,0:14:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It was unsigned and\Nit has a hand-drawn picture
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.42,0:14:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,depicting a town\Nas seen from a mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.89,0:14:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It was signed "K. P.".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.66,0:14:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,K. P...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.53,0:14:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Klaus.. .Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.56,0:14:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That is all I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.03,0:14:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Southern Germany...\NA town surrounded by mountains...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.44,0:14:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My father...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.97,0:14:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is my father\Ngoing to be killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.07,0:14:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.94,0:14:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But it won't end there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.78,0:14:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.21,0:14:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina is safe, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.28,0:14:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.11,0:15:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I want this puppet show\Nto have a happy ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.09,0:15:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Please protect Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.12,0:15:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.49,0:15:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world\Nis going to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.06,0:15:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.36,0:15:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan is trying to recreate the atrocity\Nof the Red Rose Mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.20,0:15:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the 511 Kinderheim Massacre.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.17,0:15:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.14,0:15:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what happens,\Ncome back alive, Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.58,0:15:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You saved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.48,0:15:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you must, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.12,0:15:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's begun to rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.84,0:15:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,A drink...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.97,0:16:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.41,0:16:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Crap...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.02,0:16:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How was it? Did the police\Nfind Conrad's body yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.92,0:16:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No. They're still investigating\Nhis disappearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.02,0:16:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We really shouldn't have\Nhidden him in the forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.29,0:16:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We should have informed\Nthe police at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.46,0:16:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.23,0:16:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one who thought\Nthat I shot him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.17,0:16:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly. This happened\Nbecause you won the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.30,0:16:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, you didn't have to\Nbuy these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.12,0:16:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how long you wait,\Nthe train won't come.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.29,0:16:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,All this rain flooded the railway bridge\Nover the Elgar River!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.22,0:16:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the roads are closed\Nbecause of the river flooding.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.36,0:16:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,An isolated island.. .\NThis is the worst situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.00,0:16:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Klaus Poppe, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.10,0:16:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You know of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.33,0:17:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jakub Farobek,\NEmile Scherbe...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.31,0:17:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they're\Nthe same person as Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.58,0:17:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The drawing and literary styles\Nare different, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.98,0:17:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When you become an enthusiast\Nlike me, you sort of know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.19,0:17:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why he used\Nso many pen names, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.16,0:17:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,His drawings are amusing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.79,0:17:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can never like his pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.40,0:17:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,There are tons of picture books\Nin the world with dark content.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.83,0:17:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But his books are\Na little different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.07,0:17:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How are they different?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.81,0:17:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.84,0:17:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They're filled with malice.. .\NI suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.48,0:17:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.09,0:17:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,A picture book by Helmut Voss\Nwas published in '89.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.06,0:17:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,There were very few printed,\Nso you'll seldom see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.56,0:18:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But from what I can see, he's also\Nthe same person as Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.33,0:18:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.64,0:18:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, when you become like me,\Nyou just know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.51,0:18:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how much\Nhe changes his drawing style,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.11,0:18:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,there's always a certain\Nidiosyncrasy that remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.28,0:18:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The story is completely\Ndifferent from the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.98,0:18:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A thief flees to a town nestled\Nin the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.38,0:18:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The thief plans to make\Nsome money in that town,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.09,0:18:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but as he interacts with the people\Nin the town, he forgets how to steal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.02,0:18:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And he begins to work for the people\Nof the town and lives peacefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.66,0:18:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's titled,\NThe Peaceful House.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.77,0:18:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The malice I used to get from\Nhis books is completely gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.14,0:18:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But the art is no good at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.77,0:18:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's odd. His story got better,\Nbut he can't draw anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.15,0:18:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if he\Nlost sight of his goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.48,0:18:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A Peaceful Home. ..\NA town nestled in the mountains...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.79,0:19:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Our home was a town surrounded\Nby mountains in southern Germany.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.23,0:19:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A map...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.13,0:19:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a map\Nof southern Germany?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.80,0:19:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.94,0:19:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A town nestled in the mountains\Nin southern Germany...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.64,0:19:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.58,0:19:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruhenheim...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.95,0:19:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly. It sure is raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.26,0:19:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, how did it go? Did you find out\Nwhere Conrad went?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.43,0:19:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No. We don't have any idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.70,0:19:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,My partners are searching\Nfor him right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.40,0:19:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But with this rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.10,0:19:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear that\Nthe train tracks and roads
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.14,0:19:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,aren't any good\Nbecause the river's flooded.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.37,0:19:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As his friend,\NI'm sure you must be worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.24,0:19:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, what's going on?\NIt was such a peaceful town.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.58,0:20:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It started with Conrad going missing,\Nthen Mrs. Hillman's dog was shot...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.72,0:20:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor Mrs. Hillman was\Novercome with grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.29,0:20:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that Mr. Kemnar was attacked\Nas he was leaving the pub.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.86,0:20:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard that he was\Nin serious condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.87,0:20:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We still don't know who hit him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.40,0:20:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If Mr. Kemnar died, it would have\Nbeen the first murder in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.34,0:20:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Though the situation is what it is,\Nback up won't come because of the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.34,0:20:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we to do\Nwith such few people?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.41,0:20:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got to be an outsider!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.78,0:20:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There were never any crimes\Nin this town before!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.62,0:20:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the work of an outsider!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.32,0:20:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We're outsiders, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.06,0:20:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.89,0:20:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure is raining.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.93,0:20:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go outside in this rain\Nin a wheelchair.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.77,0:20:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, I'm going to pick up\Nmy partners and patrol once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.18,0:21:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.92,0:21:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Your husband's shoes.. .\Nthey're pretty dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.49,0:21:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if he walked\Naround in the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.80,0:21:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to borrow\Nyour phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.01,0:21:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.31,0:21:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not the sort\Nto do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.80,0:21:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?\NDid you run out of gas?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.83,0:21:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Or are you out of oil?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.20,0:22:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll call a repair shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.51,0:22:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Another gunshot...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.65,0:22:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The phone's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.19,0:22:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it too late to stop it?
